modules.description: Provides functions to write to and read from the console, with support for both Unix standard output and Xen PV console ring operations. Works with byte sequences and character streams, handling low-level input and output interactions. Used to implement console logging and user input handling in system-level applications.

Provides operations to read from and write to a network console, including disconnecting, closing, and logging messages. Works with buffer structures (Cstruct.t), error types, and write error variants. Used to manage asynchronous data transmission and logging in networked applications.
